---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const analytics = await getCollection('analytics');
const sorted = analytics.sort((a, b) => (a.data.rank || 999) - (b.data.rank || 999) || a.data.name.localeCompare(b.data.name));
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Analytics Tools for Streamers - Fairly Odd Streamers"
  description="Discover the best analytics and tracking tools for livestreamers. Monitor your stream performance and audience engagement."
>

<div class="section-narrow">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Analytics Tools</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #b0b0b8; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
      Track and analyze your stream performance with these powerful analytics platforms.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-3">
      {
        sorted.map((tool) => (
          <div class="card" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; height: 100%; background: #1a1a1a; border: 1px solid #333; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
            {tool.data.photo && (
              <div style="width: 100%; height: 200px; background: #0a0a0a; overflow: hidden; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
                <img src={tool.data.photo} alt={tool.data.name} style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover;" />
              </div>
            )}
            <div style="padding: 1.5rem; flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column;">
              <h3 style="color: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; font-size: 1.25rem;">{tool.data.name}</h3>

              <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                {tool.data.featured && (
                  <span style="display: inline-block; background: #a855f7; color: white; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">Featured</span>
                )}
                {tool.data.analysisType && (
                  <span style="display: inline-block; background: #0f766e; color: white; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">{tool.data.analysisType}</span>
                )}
              </div>

              {(tool.data.shortDescription || tool.data.overview) && (
                <p style="color: #b0b0b8; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; margin: 0 0 1rem 0; flex: 1;">
                  {tool.data.shortDescription || tool.data.overview}
                </p>
              )}

              <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem;">
                {tool.data.link && (
                  <a href={tool.data.link} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display: inline-block; background: #7c3aed; color: white; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 4px; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; transition: background 0.2s;">
                    Visit Website →
                  </a>
                )}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>

    {sorted.length === 0 && <p style="text-align: center; color: #b0b0b8;">No analytics tools found.</p>}

    <div style="margin-top: 3rem; text-align: center;">
      <a href="/resources/sponsorships/" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Sponsorships</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px; margin-top: 3rem;">
<div fs-toc-element="contents"> <h2>Analytics Tools to Uncover Streamer Stats</h2> <p>Livestreaming stats and analytics are powerful tools that can provide valuable insights for Twitch streamers looking to grow their channel. By tracking and analyzing these metrics, you can gain a better understanding of your audience, improve your content, and identify new opportunities for engagement and growth.</p> <p>It&#x27;s important to note that the focus of the article is on using third-party tools to analyze other channels and uncover trends in the space - not on explaining your own channel&#x27;s stats. Although that&#x27;s a topic we&#x27;ll dive into on our blog.</p> <p>Armed with this information, you&#x27;ll be better equipped to make class="toc-marker"></div> <div fs-toc-element="contents"> <h2>Streams Charts</h2> <figure style="max-width:1370px"> <a href="https://streamscharts.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"> <div><img src="/images/streamscharts-2.png" loading="lazy" alt="StreamsCharts.com Homepage Screenshot"></div> </a> </figure> <p>Streams Charts is one of the <a href="https://streamscharts.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"><strong>largest databases of live streaming stats and analytics</strong></a>. This platform offers a variety of features to help you understand the livestreaming landscape effectively. Some key features include:</p> <ul role="list"> <li>Global and regional rankings of streamers, games, categories, platforms, etc.</li> <li>Detailed profiles of streamers, games, categories, and platforms with graphs, charts, and tables.</li> <li>Historical data and trends of viewership, followers, subscribers, donations, and more.</li> <li>Customizable filters, sorting, and search options.</li> <li>Export your data as images or excel files.</li> </ul> <p>These features enable you to deeply analyze the streaming ecosystem and make informed decisions for your streaming journey.</p> <h3>How to Use</h3> <p>There are several ways you can utilize Streams Charts to analyze livestream data and take your streaming game to the next level:</p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Compare your channel performance:</strong> Analyze your channel&#x27;s performance against other streamers in your niche or region to see where you stand and identify areas for improvement.</li> <li><strong>Find the optimal streaming factors:</strong> Examine viewership patterns to determine the best time, day, game, category, and platform to stream and maximize your outreach.</li> <li><strong>Identify popular and trending content:</strong> Keep an eye on the most popular and trending games, categories, and platforms so you can stay ahead of the curve and align your content with what your audience wants.</li> <li><strong>Track your progress and set goals:</strong> Monitor your channel&#x27;s growth over time, set realistic goals, and celebrate your achievements as you reach new milestones.</li> </ul> <p>By leveraging the power of Streams Charts and the data it offers, you can optimize your streaming strategy and grow your audience like never before.</p> </div> <div id="sullygnome" class="toc-marker"></div> <div fs-toc-element="contents"> <h2>SullyGnome</h2> <figure style="max-width:1592px"> <a href="https://sullygnome.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"> <div><img src="/images/sullygnome.png" loading="lazy" alt="SullyGnome Homepage Screenshot"></div> </a> </figure> <p>SullyGnome is a <a href="https://sullygnome.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"><strong>comprehensive source of Twitch stats and analytics</strong></a>, offering valuable insights into your favorite Twitch streamers and games.</p> <h3>Features</h3> <p>SullyGnome provides a wide range of data and features, including:</p> <ul role="list"> <li>Current and historic stats for Twitch streamers, games, categories, and teams.</li> <li>Rankings of streamers by followers, views, peak viewership, average viewership, and more.</li> <li>Live stats of current streams, viewership distribution, chat activity, and more.</li> <li>Summary reports of streamers&#x27; activity, schedule, games played, and more.</li> <li>Interactive graphs and charts showcasing various metrics and indicators.</li> </ul> <p>With such a wealth of information at your fingertips, you can gain a deep understanding of the livestreaming landscape.</p> <h3>How to Use</h3> <p>Here are some examples of how you can use SullyGnome to analyze livestreaming data:</p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Find your channel ranking:</strong> Determine how your channel compares to other streamers on Twitch in terms of followers, views, and other metrics.</li> <li><strong>Analyze your stream:</strong> Look into your stream quality, consistency, engagement, retention, and other crucial aspects to identify areas for improvement.</li> <li><strong>Discover new games or categories:</strong> Explore different games or categories that may suit your style and audience preferences, helping you expand your reach and grow your channel.</li> <li><strong>Learn from successful streamers:</strong> Study the strategies and best practices of top performers on Twitch, so you can emulate their techniques and accelerate your progress.</li> </ul> <p>Remember, the key to success in livestreaming is understanding your audience and adapting your content to keep them engaged. With SullyGnome, you can thoroughly analyze your channel and the broader Twitch landscape, making informed decisions for the betterment of your streaming career.</p> </div> <div id="twitchtracker" class="toc-marker"></div> <div fs-toc-element="contents"> <h2>TwitchTracker</h2> <figure style="max-width:1187px"> <a href="https://twitchtracker.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"> <div><img src="/images/twitchtracker.png" loading="lazy" alt="TwitchTracker Homepage Screenshot"></div> </a> </figure> <p>TwitchTracker is a reliable source for <a href="https://twitchtracker.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"><strong>livestreaming stats and analytics</strong></a>, offering users a comprehensive view of Twitch channels, games, and global statistics. With a user-friendly interface, it presents information in the form of tables, charts, and graphs to help you understand the state of Twitch as a platform.</p> <h3>Features</h3> <p>Using TwitchTracker, you can access a variety of data related to Twitch, including:</p> <ul role="list"> <li>Twitch statistics and charts for languages, viewership, channels, stream time, and more.</li> <li>Twitch growth and achievements over the years.</li> <li>Detailed stats and graphs for individual Twitch channels.</li> <li>Popularity trends and top streamers for Twitch games.</li> <li>Viewership trends and top streamers for Twitch categories.</li> <li>Recommended games to stream that can potentially enhance your visibility on the Twitch platform.</li> </ul> <p>These features help you gain insights into the platform&#x27;s overall performance while also providing valuable information about your channel and the Twitch community as a whole.</p> <h3>How to Use</h3> <p>TwitchTracker can be utilized in several ways to analyze livestreaming data and make informed decisions. Some of these include:</p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Understanding the overall state and direction of Twitch as a platform</strong>, allowing you to anticipate changes and adapt your strategies accordingly.</li> <li><strong>Evaluating your channel&#x27;s performance and potential in relation to Twitch&#x27;s growth</strong>, giving you the information needed to improve and grow your audience.</li> <li><strong>Discovering which languages or regions have the most or least viewership on Twitch</strong>, aiding in the decision-making process for targeting specific demographics or expanding your reach.</li> <li><strong>Exploring new or niche games and categories with high demand or low supply on Twitch</strong>, potentially helping you find untapped markets and increase viewership.</li> </ul> <p>By leveraging the features and data provided by TwitchTracker, you can make more informed decisions, optimize your content, and grow your channel on the Twitch platform.</p> </div> <div id="streambee" class="toc-marker"></div> <div fs-toc-element="contents"> <h2>StreamBee</h2> <figure style="max-width:1440pxpx"> <a href="https://streambee.io/" target="_blank"> <div><img src="/images/streambee-preview.png" loading="lazy" alt="StreamBee Homepage Screenshot"></div> </a> </figure> <p> <a href="https://streambee.io/" target="_blank"><strong>StreamBee</strong></a> allows you to understand your audience better and pinpoint areas for growth. When you sign up, which is free (with a paid plan option), you can easily access an array of valuable information. And the best part about it? The dashboard UI is sleek and very easy to uncover actionable insights. Some key features include: </p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Stream overview dashboard</strong>: Each stream has a grade where you also see hours watched, sub growth, follower growth, peak viewers, number of clips, plus a lot more.</li> <li><strong>Engagement analytics</strong>: See how your audience interacts with your content. Breaks down super chatters, engaged chatters, casual chatters, not-engaged chatters and lurkers. </li> <li><strong>When to stream</strong>: Find out the ideal time for you to stream and get feedback on how long you should be streaming to optimize efficiency.</li> <li><strong>Clips and emotes statistics</strong>: Figoure out the best category and time of your stream that brought you most of the clip and emote interactions.</li> <li><strong>VOD review</strong>: Analyze your stream and find positive, neutral or harmful patterns in your stream. This unique feature looks for outliers in your data to tell you when something went great or wrong.</li> </ul> <h3>How to Use</h3> <p>StreamBee gives you data that helps you make better content and grow across all platfomrms. Here&#x27;s a few ways how you can use the tool:</p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Discover the best games to stream on Twitch</strong>: StreamBee takes your time streamed, hours watched, and followers gained to create suggestions on the best games that&#x27;ll increase your viewer and follower count.</li> <li><strong>Viewers breakdown</strong>: Are you a small streamer with less data for insights? The viewers breakdown tool is perfect to see how many regular, casual and new viewers visit your streams.</li> <li><strong>Cross-platform analytics</strong>: Track your growth and reach across all the platforms you stream to or post content to. Includes Twitch, YouTube, Discord, Twitter, Instagram and TikTok.</li> <li><strong>Analytics for stream managers</strong>: If you manage a group of livestreamers, StreamBee offers in-depth Twitch data for each of them in a single reporting dashboard with cross-platform insights.</li> </ul> <p>StreamBee is a great tool for any Twitch streamer looking for valuable insights to grow their channel. Why not use it and see what it suggests? It&#x27;s free after all.</p> </div> <div id="kickanalyst" class="toc-marker"></div> <div fs-toc-element="contents"> <h2>KickAnalyst</h2> <figure style="max-width:1069px"> <a href="https://kickanalyst.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"> <div><img src="/images/kickanalyst-homepage.png" loading="lazy" alt="KickAnalyst Homepage Screenshot"></div> </a> </figure> <p> <a href="https://kickanalyst.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"><strong>KickAnalyst</strong></a><strong> </strong>is a valuable source of livestreaming stats and analytics for the relatively new streaming platform, Kick. KickAnalyst offers minimal data and features for now but they are building a robust platform that will become a great resource for analyzing trends on Kick. </p> <h3>Features</h3> <p>KickAnalyst has a variety of features designed to help you make the most of your Kick streaming experience, including:</p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Streamer analytics dashboard</strong>: This dashboard provides essential metrics and insights to help you monitor your channel&#x27;s performance and growth.</li> <li><strong>Category and game rankings dashboard</strong>: Lists all the categories and games that are most viewed on Kick&#x27;s platform.</li> <li><strong>Channels dashboard</strong>: Ranking the highest average viewership for Kick streamers over the last 30 days, with a language filter.</li> <li><strong>Clips dashboard</strong>: See the most viewed Kick clips of all time.</li> </ul> <h3>How to Use</h3> <p>KickAnalyst is designed to be user-friendly and practical. Here are a few examples of how you can utilize the platform to analyze livestreaming data:</p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Monitor your channel&#x27;s health and growth</strong>: Use the streamer analytics dashboard to keep track of key metrics and insights, providing you with a clear picture of your channel&#x27;s performance.</li> <li><strong>Benchmark your performance</strong>: Compare your channel&#x27;s progress with similar or competitive streamers using the streamer comparison tool to identify areas you can improve in.</li> </ul> <p>By utilizing KickAnalyst and its features, you&#x27;ll be able to make informed decisions, boost your channel&#x27;s performance, and connect with like-minded individuals on the Kick platform.</p> </div> <div id="other-tools" class="toc-marker"></div> <div fs-toc-element="contents"> <h2>Other Tools</h2> <p>There are several other tools available that provide analytics on Twitch and other livestreaming platforms. Here are some of the other tools we check out from time to time and thought they may be of interest to the streaming community.</p> <h3>R1CH&#x27;s Twitch Analyzer</h3> <p> <a href="https://r-1.ch/analyzer/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"><strong>R1CH&#x27;s Twitch Analyzer</strong></a> allows you to check the technical quality and stability of your Twitch stream. It will check and diagnose the following items: </p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Bitrate stability</strong>. See how stable your video bitrate is. Unstable bitrates can cause lag for viewers.</li> <li><strong>Dropped frames</strong>. Check for dropped frames, which cause lag and missing video segments for viewers.</li> <li><strong>Keyframe check</strong>. Verify your keyframe interval is set correctly. Incorrect keyframe interval can result in long stream delays and poor viewer interaction.</li> <li><strong>Duplicate frames</strong>. Check for any duplicated frames, which may indicate you are encoding at a higher FPS than your content is rendering at, causing stuttering.</li> <li><strong>Video frame rate</strong>. Check the stability of your video FPS. Slow capture methods or an overworked CPU can cause low or unstable FPS.</li> <li><strong>Quality check</strong>. Calculate whether you have sufficient bitrate for good quality, your resolution is correct and your audio is good.</li> <li><strong>Stream info</strong>. See the bitrate, resolution, FPS, audio codec, uptime, transcodes and other useful information about the stream.</li> </ul> <h3>SocialBlade</h3> <p> <a href="https://socialblade.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"><strong>SocialBlade</strong></a><strong> </strong>tracks user statistics for YouTube, Twitch, Instagram, and Twitter. It gives you a deeper understanding of user growth and trends. </p> <p>SocialBlade allows you to track your follower and view count over time across all these platforms. You can use this information to check specific dates against your content.</p> <p>For example, did you get a lot of views on one day, or a lot of new followers? Great! Go back and look at what you were doing differently on that day so you can see if it’ll be possible to replicate that in the future.</p> <h3>StreamElements Chat Stats</h3> <p> <a href="https://stats.streamelements.com/?ref=FairlyOddStreamers" target="_blank"><strong>StreamElements Chat Stats</strong></a> has been collecting data from Twitch Chat since January 9th, 2016. It only reports on chat stats, which seems a bit silly but is incredibly useful and shouldn&#x27;t be ignored. </p> <ul role="list"> <li><strong>Find out who your top chatters are</strong> by looking up your channel. You can reward the most active community members by giving them a VIP badge in your chat.</li> <li><strong>Find the most active members in chat</strong> and consider adding them to your mod team since you know they&#x27;re engaged with you and your community.</li> <li>See the most popular emotes used in your chat. </li> <li>Get ideas for custom emotes. For example, if you don&#x27;t have a laughing emote and see that one of the most used emotes in your chat is LUL, you should consider making a custom laughing emote for your community to use.</li> </ul> <h2>Conclusion</h2> <p>There are many different tools available for streamers to track analytics. We recommend using these tools to supplement the existing Twitch dashboard, allowing you to figure out what you’re doing right and what areas you can improve.</p> <p>You can also use each of these tools to compare your own stream to other similar streamers, perhaps people who stream the same games as you or who have a similar audience.</p> <p>However, always be careful when comparing yourself to others: as we’ve mentioned a few times here, everyone’s journey on Twitch is different, and Twitch is incredibly unpredictable. Use the data to inform you, rather than to define you.</p> <p>You could also use the information provided by these tools to identify streamers who might make great friends you could learn from, or even find a team of streamers to work with.</p> <p>All of these tools should be used wisely. While they’re not completely accurate, third party tools are often used by brands to decide whether or not to work with a streamer or content creator, so it’s great to be familiar with each of them so you’re well-equipped when talking with a potential sponsor.</p> </div>
  </div>
</div>
</BaseLayout>
